WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.000
Created by ©Yozuki  |  #VisitUs  t.me/Yozukilk

2
00:00:19.720 --> 00:00:24.170
'Tis time for torture, Princess.

3
00:00:38.180 --> 00:00:45.500
'Tis Time for "Torture," Princess

4
00:01:59.970 --> 00:02:05.060
Princess, today's torture 
is beach sword fighting.

5
00:02:05.770 --> 00:02:07.390
The rules are simple.

6
00:02:07.390 --> 00:02:10.270
Pop the balloons on your 
opponents’ heads to win.

7
00:02:08.310 --> 00:02:11.610
Lieutorment
Youki

8
00:02:08.310 --> 00:02:11.610
Lieutorment
Inki

9
00:02:10.270 --> 00:02:11.610
How is this torture, exactly?

10
00:02:12.110 --> 00:02:14.730
Your opponents shall be Youki and Inki.

11
00:02:14.730 --> 00:02:19.410
Should you lose, Princess, you will 
divulge the empire's secrets.

12
00:02:19.410 --> 00:02:23.330
I see. So, what if I win?

13
00:02:23.330 --> 00:02:25.910
You think you can win?

14
00:02:25.910 --> 00:02:27.200
Snicker.

15
00:02:27.200 --> 00:02:28.000
What?

16
00:02:29.040 --> 00:02:34.710
We're champions of the Hell-Lord's 
beach sword fighting tag team tournament.

17
00:02:34.710 --> 00:02:36.850
F-For two years in a row.

18
00:02:36.850 --> 00:02:41.590
5th Hell-Lord's Beach Sword Fighting Tournament

19
00:02:37.670 --> 00:02:41.010
Sounds like the Hell-Lord 
holds some fun events.

20
00:02:41.590 --> 00:02:45.010
W-We're the strongest members 
of the Hellhorde's forces.

21
00:02:45.010 --> 00:02:49.290
There's no way you can defeat us!

22
00:02:50.560 --> 00:02:53.020
You heard them.

23
00:02:53.020 --> 00:02:56.230
Very well. In the event you win,

24
00:02:56.500 --> 00:02:58.860
I shall grant you any request.

25
00:02:59.150 --> 00:03:01.110
Anything?

26
00:03:01.110 --> 00:03:04.030
Yes. I shall even set you free.

27
00:03:04.030 --> 00:03:05.240
Well, well.

28
00:03:09.660 --> 00:03:11.950
Let the battle begin!

29
00:03:13.710 --> 00:03:17.340
Let's go, In-chan. We’ll 
start with Strategy B-shift.

30
00:03:17.340 --> 00:03:18.380
Got it.

31
00:03:18.800 --> 00:03:22.800
<i>With Strategy B, I draw the enemy's 
attention with my swift movements...</i>

32
00:03:22.800 --> 00:03:23.800
<i>While I—</i>

33
00:03:25.970 --> 00:03:26.810
What?

34
00:03:28.630 --> 00:03:29.840
No way.

35
00:03:30.270 --> 00:03:31.690
What did you expect?

36
00:03:31.690 --> 00:03:35.970
Her Highness is the Princess and
Commander of the Imperial Third Legion.

37
00:03:37.400 --> 00:03:39.750
There's no way just the two 
of you could defeat her.

38
00:03:39.750 --> 00:03:44.370
S-So you really are a commander.

39
00:03:44.370 --> 00:03:45.490
Rude!

40
00:03:46.330 --> 00:03:48.730
Since I was a young girl,

41
00:03:48.730 --> 00:03:52.990
I was trained in the art of the sword by 
top-class swordsmen of the Imperial Army.

42
00:03:58.420 --> 00:04:00.710
Spin ten times, and then start running.

43
00:04:00.710 --> 00:04:03.800
Whoever touches the tree first wins.

44
00:04:03.800 --> 00:04:04.960
Teach her to use a sword.

45
00:04:04.960 --> 00:04:08.290
Whoever reaches the tree first gets all 
of tonight's dessert to themselves.

46
00:04:08.290 --> 00:04:09.560
Learn to use a sword!

47
00:04:13.690 --> 00:04:15.150
There!

48
00:04:15.440 --> 00:04:18.270
I win!

49
00:04:18.270 --> 00:04:20.940
Jimochi taught me everything there is to know

50
00:04:20.940 --> 00:04:23.780
about swordplay and the brutality of combat.

51
00:04:24.860 --> 00:04:28.240
There's no way you could defeat me.

52
00:04:28.240 --> 00:04:30.700
Based on that anecdote, 
I think they could beat you.

53
00:04:32.080 --> 00:04:35.120
It’s just you now, You-chan.

54
00:04:36.290 --> 00:04:40.000
Princess-chan, remember the rules.

55
00:04:40.000 --> 00:04:43.930
Pop the balloons to win. 
There are no other rules.

56
00:04:44.840 --> 00:04:48.220
I summon thee, my final weapon!

57
00:04:48.850 --> 00:04:53.230
In other words, all that matters 
is that you pop the balloons!

58
00:04:53.060 --> 00:04:54.600
Gatling Water Gun

59
00:04:53.060 --> 00:04:54.600
Youki Custom

60
00:04:54.600 --> 00:04:59.390
This water gun can fire 45 shots per second.

61
00:05:04.020 --> 00:05:06.400
I win! Victory is mine!

62
00:05:07.910 --> 00:05:09.160
What?!

63
00:05:09.160 --> 00:05:13.080
Oh, no. After all we've been 
through, I'd forgotten.

64
00:05:13.080 --> 00:05:18.330
The Princess’ swordsmanship is truly 
top-level, even for the Imperial Army!

65
00:05:19.210 --> 00:05:20.820
She’s a proper warrior!

66
00:05:22.000 --> 00:05:24.090
Crud. I'm out of ammo.

67
00:05:25.090 --> 00:05:29.050
<i>At this rate, I'll be forced 
to release the Princess.</i>

68
00:05:29.510 --> 00:05:31.890
<i>I must join the fight.</i>

69
00:05:32.310 --> 00:05:33.600
<i>No, I can't.</i>

70
00:05:33.600 --> 00:05:38.690
<i>When I first explained the rules, I said 
her opponents would be Youki and Inki.</i>

71
00:05:39.860 --> 00:05:40.980
<i>What should I do?</i>

72
00:05:43.070 --> 00:05:47.240
Ignore the rules. 
Do whatever it takes to win.

73
00:05:47.240 --> 00:05:49.490
<i>The devil on my shoulder.</i>

74
00:05:49.990 --> 00:05:57.500
Torture Party

75
00:05:50.660 --> 00:05:53.450
You must only make an effort 
to keep your public promises.

76
00:05:53.450 --> 00:05:55.160
You needn't actually keep them.

77
00:05:55.160 --> 00:05:57.500
<i>The politician on my shoulder.</i>

78
00:05:57.500 --> 00:06:02.420
Besides, it would be no fun 
if she won too easily.

79
00:06:02.420 --> 00:06:03.250
<i>The writer.</i>

80
00:06:03.460 --> 00:06:07.590
With passion, we can change 
the world, and even rules.

81
00:06:07.590 --> 00:06:08.680
<i>The revolutionary.</i>

82
00:06:11.220 --> 00:06:12.550
<i>They're right.</i>

83
00:06:13.310 --> 00:06:17.940
Releasing the Princess 
is out of the question.

84
00:06:20.730 --> 00:06:24.070
It sure feels nice to move around.

85
00:06:24.820 --> 00:06:27.190
This is fun!

86
00:06:29.530 --> 00:06:32.370
It’s time to end this, You-chan.

87
00:06:33.240 --> 00:06:37.450
Hold up, Princess-chan!

88
00:06:39.020 --> 00:06:40.180
Crab

89
00:06:41.130 --> 00:06:44.630
Hell-Lord's Daughter
Ultimate Hyper Legendary
Cadet Harm-Marshal
Maomao-chan

90
00:06:41.130 --> 00:06:44.630
Krall Regiment
Combat Soldier
Mad Wolf

91
00:06:41.330 --> 00:06:43.790
Prepare yourself!

92
00:06:44.630 --> 00:06:47.130
Beastmaster
Krall

93
00:06:44.630 --> 00:06:47.130
Combat Soldier
Fourth Class
&
Pain-Private
Giant

94
00:06:47.130 --> 00:06:49.630
Torturer's Aide
Datarma

95
00:06:47.130 --> 00:06:49.800
Hellholm Cafeteria Staff
Kitchen Sub-Leader
Mad Kaiser

96
00:06:50.260 --> 00:06:52.090
Weaponsmith and Pain-Private
Gilga

97
00:06:52.090 --> 00:06:54.600
Grand Inquisitor
Torture Tortura

98
00:06:54.600 --> 00:06:56.600
A Passing Seagull

99
00:06:56.600 --> 00:06:57.840
Guys!

100
00:06:58.180 --> 00:07:01.300
We won't let you have your 
way any longer, Princess.

101
00:07:01.730 --> 00:07:04.570
All right. Bring it on, all of you.

102
00:07:04.570 --> 00:07:06.940
Go, You-chan!

103
00:07:04.570 --> 00:07:07.480
Disqualified

104
00:07:06.940 --> 00:07:07.490
What?!

105
00:07:07.490 --> 00:07:09.610
You can do it, Your Highness!

106
00:07:12.070 --> 00:07:13.410
Gotcha!

107
00:07:13.820 --> 00:07:15.730
On your guard, Princess-chan!

108
00:07:15.730 --> 00:07:17.870
Too easy, Krall-chan!

109
00:07:23.330 --> 00:07:24.670
I knew you would slide!

110
00:07:24.670 --> 00:07:25.200
Gotcha!

111
00:07:28.380 --> 00:07:30.130
And I knew you would do that.

112
00:07:36.060 --> 00:07:37.510
You-chan's in trouble.

113
00:07:39.850 --> 00:07:41.600
If this is how it’s gonna be…

114
00:07:41.600 --> 00:07:43.690
It’s a free-for-all!

115
00:08:01.200 --> 00:08:03.960
Stop right there!

116
00:08:05.500 --> 00:08:07.920
Princess!

117
00:08:07.920 --> 00:08:09.460
This is so much fun!

118
00:08:10.880 --> 00:08:13.220
I caught you!

119
00:08:11.590 --> 00:08:14.260
You caught me!

120
00:08:15.640 --> 00:08:20.470
The Princess
had fun

121
00:08:41.120 --> 00:08:43.460
That was so much fun.

122
00:08:52.630 --> 00:08:55.050
Wait, what? What happened to being released?

123
00:09:06.400 --> 00:09:07.860
Your Highness.

124
00:09:08.230 --> 00:09:13.240
Previously and the time before that, 
I failed because I was too focused on my spell.

125
00:09:14.780 --> 00:09:16.030
But this time,

126
00:09:16.570 --> 00:09:23.910
I, Louch Brittan, the White Knight, 
will be sure to save you.

127
00:09:17.990 --> 00:09:23.910
Imperial
First
Legion

128
00:09:17.990 --> 00:09:23.910
Louch
Brittan

129
00:09:26.420 --> 00:09:29.670
Who are you?

130
00:09:34.420 --> 00:09:38.010
<i>I couldn't sense him at all.</i>

131
00:09:44.270 --> 00:09:47.100
'Tis Time for "Torture," Princess

132
00:09:48.480 --> 00:09:51.110
You’re a human, aren't you?

133
00:09:51.110 --> 00:09:53.860
What are you doing here?

134
00:09:53.860 --> 00:09:57.910
<i>A demon. His presence is overpowering.</i>

135
00:09:57.910 --> 00:09:59.740
<i>He's no ordinary demon.</i>

136
00:10:00.740 --> 00:10:01.670
First strike.

137
00:10:02.200 --> 00:10:03.870
Holy Moon!

138
00:10:07.920 --> 00:10:09.380
Are you perhaps lost?

139
00:10:12.540 --> 00:10:13.870
Settle down.

140
00:10:13.870 --> 00:10:18.720
I understand why a human would feel 
uneasy if they wandered into this place.

141
00:10:19.640 --> 00:10:21.470
Brittan Clan Swordstyle,

142
00:10:22.050 --> 00:10:26.140
Lightning Hurricane!

143
00:10:23.390 --> 00:10:26.140
<i>Lightning Hurricane</i>

144
00:10:26.390 --> 00:10:29.310
I just happened by here.

145
00:10:28.060 --> 00:10:38.360
Lightning Hurricane! Lightning 
Hurricane! Lightning Hurricane!

146
00:10:29.310 --> 00:10:31.910
I did not come to harm you.

147
00:10:31.910 --> 00:10:35.030
I was out attending a voice 
actor's release event.

148
00:10:35.030 --> 00:10:38.360
I simply came across you on my way back.

149
00:10:38.360 --> 00:10:39.860
Release event?

150
00:10:40.530 --> 00:10:44.790
Normally, I watch quietly from 
the back with my arms folded,

151
00:10:44.790 --> 00:10:47.710
but today, I moved up a 
bit towards the front.

152
00:10:48.210 --> 00:10:53.040
Because I did, I felt more 
like a part of the concert.

153
00:10:53.040 --> 00:10:54.710
Geh-heh-heh.

154
00:10:57.090 --> 00:10:59.840
<i>A demon would never attend a release event.</i>

155
00:10:59.840 --> 00:11:02.500
<i>It must be some kind of 
terrible code word.</i>

156
00:11:03.140 --> 00:11:04.220
<i>In that case…</i>

157
00:11:06.060 --> 00:11:08.350
Focusing mana.

158
00:11:12.060 --> 00:11:13.900
White Knight Magic,

159
00:11:14.320 --> 00:11:16.320
Holy Shine!

160
00:11:14.570 --> 00:11:16.320
<i>Holy Shine</i>

161
00:11:28.660 --> 00:11:29.830
That should do it.

162
00:11:31.960 --> 00:11:34.710
Have you settled down some?

163
00:11:34.710 --> 00:11:35.830
Impossible.

164
00:11:37.960 --> 00:11:39.660
The recoil from my attack—

165
00:11:52.480 --> 00:11:55.610
Why did you save me? I'm a human.

166
00:11:55.610 --> 00:11:59.530
Geh-heh-heh. Your life has 
value, just like mine.

167
00:11:59.530 --> 00:12:03.150
Besides, that adornment on your neck…

168
00:12:05.780 --> 00:12:08.620
It’s the emblem of the protagonist's unit

169
00:12:08.620 --> 00:12:11.830
from the Mobile Cavalry Soul 
Cross anime, is it not?

170
00:12:12.540 --> 00:12:15.540
Mobile Cavalry Soul Cross

171
00:12:16.170 --> 00:12:17.590
How do you know that?

172
00:12:17.590 --> 00:12:21.670
No one’s ever noticed before because 
it blends in with the rest of my outfit!

173
00:12:21.670 --> 00:12:23.380
Geh-heh-heh.

174
00:12:23.380 --> 00:12:25.640
I have one as well.

175
00:12:28.250 --> 00:12:33.560
This emblem is truly well-made. It 
looks just like it does in the anime.

176
00:12:33.560 --> 00:12:34.270
You get it!

177
00:12:34.770 --> 00:12:38.980
I have thoughts about items from 
anime being turned into merch.

178
00:12:38.980 --> 00:12:41.890
I wish they would stop including 
pictures of characters.

179
00:12:41.890 --> 00:12:45.240
The inclusion of such images 
ruins the world building.

180
00:12:45.240 --> 00:12:48.780
I wish to own the same 
items as the characters.

181
00:12:48.780 --> 00:12:49.860
Exactly!

182
00:12:54.580 --> 00:12:56.830
I apologize for suddenly attacking you.

183
00:12:56.830 --> 00:12:59.330
Geh-heh-heh. It’s fine.

184
00:13:10.350 --> 00:13:17.440
<i>I see. Not all demons are bad, 
nor are they my enemies.</i>

185
00:13:18.810 --> 00:13:21.650
<i>Only the Hell-Lord and his 
forces are my enemies.</i>

186
00:13:22.230 --> 00:13:25.320
<i>I mustn't fail to recognize that.</i>

187
00:13:26.530 --> 00:13:28.070
Well, I suppose I should leave.

188
00:13:28.070 --> 00:13:31.330
Didn't you have something to do here?

189
00:13:31.330 --> 00:13:34.710
I've spent too long here already. 
I'll return another day.

190
00:13:35.500 --> 00:13:37.250
If we meet again…

191
00:13:38.580 --> 00:13:41.220
Let's discuss anime once more.

192
00:13:41.220 --> 00:13:44.330
Geh-heh-heh. Of course.

193
00:13:49.090 --> 00:13:59.360
Geh-heh-heh, scrub-a-heh-heh.

194
00:13:59.650 --> 00:14:02.650
Papa's in a good mood.

195
00:14:02.650 --> 00:14:05.230
He said he made a new friend.

196
00:14:08.910 --> 00:14:13.740
Mobile Cavalry Soul Cross

197
00:14:11.330 --> 00:14:13.740
'Tis Time for "Torture," Princess

198
00:14:21.630 --> 00:14:23.750
Yes! A match!

199
00:14:23.750 --> 00:14:27.170
That’s three in a row. 
That just leaves six more.

200
00:14:23.800 --> 00:14:28.090
Harm-Marshal
Vanilla Peschutz

201
00:14:27.170 --> 00:14:29.970
I shall find the remaining matches 
in one go, without any errors.

202
00:14:34.060 --> 00:14:35.470
Another pair.

203
00:14:36.730 --> 00:14:40.440
Nothing beats playing memory with cards.

204
00:14:42.480 --> 00:14:44.360
Besides, I can play by myself.

205
00:14:45.070 --> 00:14:48.490
I wonder if it would be 
more fun with friends.

206
00:14:49.700 --> 00:14:51.490
What am I thinking?

207
00:14:51.490 --> 00:14:54.710
I am the daughter of the 
noble House of Peschutz.

208
00:14:55.160 --> 00:14:56.370
I need no friends.

209
00:14:56.950 --> 00:15:01.880
Papa and Mama often tell me to enjoy 
myself unfettered by the family name,

210
00:15:01.880 --> 00:15:05.710
but my pride would never allow that.

211
00:15:07.880 --> 00:15:08.840
But…

212
00:15:10.260 --> 00:15:13.140
The amusement park sure was fun.

213
00:15:14.970 --> 00:15:16.430
Princess…

214
00:15:17.060 --> 00:15:20.010
I know. I'll use this to torture her.

215
00:15:20.010 --> 00:15:22.350
That’s right, it’s torture.

216
00:15:22.350 --> 00:15:24.770
It’s not that I want to play with her.

217
00:15:25.570 --> 00:15:28.030
Time for your torture, Princess!

218
00:15:29.780 --> 00:15:33.450
Today's torture is playing cards.

219
00:15:33.450 --> 00:15:36.540
If you tell me your secrets, 
you can play cards with me.

220
00:15:37.370 --> 00:15:39.290
What kind of torture is that?

221
00:15:39.290 --> 00:15:41.790
Do you truly believe Her Highness 
would divulge her secrets

222
00:15:41.790 --> 00:15:43.880
just because she wants to play cards?

223
00:15:43.880 --> 00:15:45.960
Cards are fun, aren't they?

224
00:15:45.960 --> 00:15:46.800
Your Highness?

225
00:15:46.800 --> 00:15:48.010
Speaking of cards…

226
00:15:50.470 --> 00:15:54.380
I can't play any cards because 
I'm stuck here and here.

227
00:15:54.380 --> 00:15:58.520
My, my. Whatever could be stopping you?

228
00:15:58.020 --> 00:15:59.390
It’s you, Jimochi!

229
00:15:59.680 --> 00:16:01.440
What will you do?

230
00:16:01.440 --> 00:16:05.020
You can only pass one more 
time, Your Highness.

231
00:16:05.020 --> 00:16:07.190
Will you pass again?

232
00:16:09.400 --> 00:16:10.030
Pass.

233
00:16:10.030 --> 00:16:12.320
I win!

234
00:16:12.320 --> 00:16:18.080
At this rate, tomorrow night's 
dessert will be all mine as well.

235
00:16:18.660 --> 00:16:23.040
I want dessert!

236
00:16:24.170 --> 00:16:26.090
The frustration of defeat.

237
00:16:26.090 --> 00:16:30.260
Every tear I shed made my mind stronger.

238
00:16:30.260 --> 00:16:34.050
Your Highness, you must've really 
regretted not eating that dessert.

239
00:16:34.050 --> 00:16:36.760
That’s just how fun playing cards is.

240
00:16:36.760 --> 00:16:37.600
What?

241
00:16:37.970 --> 00:16:41.640
Oh, but that doesn't mean 
I'd reveal any secrets.

242
00:16:41.640 --> 00:16:44.480
I can resist playing cards.

243
00:16:44.480 --> 00:16:45.980
Are you sure about that?

244
00:16:45.980 --> 00:16:52.650
BADOOM

245
00:16:46.360 --> 00:16:50.820
Anyway, it’s an attractive 
invitation, but I must decline.

246
00:16:50.820 --> 00:16:52.650
What? But…

247
00:16:52.950 --> 00:16:56.280
Playing with cards is fun. Really fun.

248
00:16:56.280 --> 00:17:01.120
It can be something basic, like what 
you had for breakfast this morning.

249
00:17:01.120 --> 00:17:03.040
I probably shouldn't be saying this,

250
00:17:03.040 --> 00:17:06.130
but that's not a secret you 
need to extract from me.

251
00:17:07.290 --> 00:17:10.300
Wait a minute. Do you want 
to play cards with me?

252
00:17:11.510 --> 00:17:13.590
O-Obviously not!

253
00:17:13.590 --> 00:17:17.390
It’s not like I want to 
play Old Maid together,

254
00:17:17.390 --> 00:17:20.560
which can only be played 
with at least two players.

255
00:17:20.560 --> 00:17:23.430
I definitely don't want to 
play President or Speed either.

256
00:17:23.430 --> 00:17:25.270
Just laying it all out there, aren't you?

257
00:17:25.890 --> 00:17:29.060
If you want to play, then 
you should just say so.

258
00:17:29.060 --> 00:17:32.690
I am the daughter of the 
noble House of Peschutz.

259
00:17:33.150 --> 00:17:36.700
I don't experience the 
flippant desire to play cards.

260
00:17:36.700 --> 00:17:40.080
A proud lady like myself needs no friends!

261
00:17:42.910 --> 00:17:45.580
All right. I'll tell you a secret.

262
00:17:45.580 --> 00:17:46.750
Your Highness?

263
00:17:47.540 --> 00:17:54.050
I also believed that a proud 
knight like myself needs no friends.

264
00:17:54.800 --> 00:17:55.720
But…

265
00:18:10.230 --> 00:18:11.520
The truth is…

266
00:18:14.570 --> 00:18:16.320
I wanted friends.

267
00:18:26.460 --> 00:18:28.000
Me, too.

268
00:18:38.930 --> 00:18:41.640
Come on. I've told you my secret.

269
00:18:42.510 --> 00:18:43.850
Let's play.

270
00:18:45.430 --> 00:18:46.600
Okay.

271
00:18:51.440 --> 00:18:53.610
Which card is the Joker?

272
00:18:53.610 --> 00:18:55.820
Hey, that's not fair.

273
00:18:55.820 --> 00:18:57.740
Come on, hurry up.

274
00:18:58.070 --> 00:19:00.910
Let's see. This one.

275
00:19:00.910 --> 00:19:03.950
Oh? You're sure you want that one?

276
00:19:03.950 --> 00:19:06.000
Ah, I see.

277
00:19:06.000 --> 00:19:08.120
Uh, um…

278
00:19:08.120 --> 00:19:09.470
Actually, I want this one.

279
00:19:13.040 --> 00:19:15.380
Vanilla made
a friend

280
00:19:15.670 --> 00:19:20.550
I see. So the Princess wanted friends.

281
00:19:20.550 --> 00:19:21.590
Yes, Your Majesty.

282
00:19:21.590 --> 00:19:26.390
Perhaps she'd been avoiding it until 
now since she'd been betrayed before.

283
00:19:26.390 --> 00:19:28.270
Geh-heh-heh.

284
00:19:28.270 --> 00:19:32.600
I'm glad she made a friend.

285
00:21:09.950 --> 00:21:12.530
Send off the report...

286
00:21:09.950 --> 00:21:12.960
Send Daily
Report

287
00:21:13.340 --> 00:21:15.180
And work is done.

288
00:21:20.180 --> 00:21:22.710
<i>What should I have for dinner?</i>

289
00:21:23.500 --> 00:21:28.150
<i>Tonight, I have business outside the 
house, so perhaps I'll eat out.</i>

290
00:21:52.910 --> 00:21:54.410
Meal Tickets

291
00:21:56.570 --> 00:21:58.010
Welcome.

292
00:22:04.930 --> 00:22:08.920
<i>A roast beef bowl. I didn't 
know they offered that.</i>

293
00:22:09.770 --> 00:22:14.760
<i>Curry. Come to think of it, I often 
hear the curry is delicious as well.</i>

294
00:22:15.340 --> 00:22:17.590
<i>Perhaps I'll order some next time.</i>

295
00:22:18.040 --> 00:22:24.770
<i>But I end up ordering the same thing 
despite thinking that every time.</i>

296
00:22:25.980 --> 00:22:27.540
Thanks for waiting.

297
00:22:29.070 --> 00:22:30.540
<i>A chicken and egg bowl.</i>

298
00:22:30.970 --> 00:22:33.510
<i>I've tried all kinds 
of chicken and egg bowls,</i>

299
00:22:33.510 --> 00:22:37.550
<i>but nothing beats the chicken and egg 
bowl served by this beef bowl chain.</i>

300
00:22:38.740 --> 00:22:43.240
<i>This spoon that makes it so easy 
to eat is a delight as well.</i>

301
00:22:51.020 --> 00:22:54.000
<i>Yes, this. This was the right choice.</i>

302
00:22:55.200 --> 00:23:01.680
<i>The strength of chains is their ability to 
provide the exact same flavor you imagine every time.</i>

303
00:23:02.370 --> 00:23:08.330
<i>After eating more than half, add a sprinkle 
of soy sauce to modify the flavor.</i>

304
00:23:08.640 --> 00:23:11.090
<i>Now it’s time for round two.</i>

305
00:23:24.510 --> 00:23:29.270
<i>Since it’s a bit chilly tonight, 
I can tell how warm my stomach feels.</i>

306
00:23:29.960 --> 00:23:31.090
<i>Now then.</i>

307
00:23:30.340 --> 00:23:35.340
